      "content": "but mainstream science always lags behind huge shifts like this. i'm not talking about random damage, i mean like a targeted reconfiguration. i've been reading about how high-energy particles can act as catalysts for specific biological structures. if the radiation hit at a precise moment in my sleep cycle, couldn't it have triggered an epigenetic change that basically unlocked my brain's full potential? it feels way too consistent to be a coincidence.",
